title: Leading Nuclear Energy Producer
description: In 2023, France generated 64.17% of its electricity from nuclear sources, making it one of the top producers of nuclear energy globally.

title: Near-Universal Female Primary Education Enrollment
description: As of 2016, France achieved a 99.65% adjusted net enrollment rate for primary school-aged girls, indicating almost universal access to primary education for females.

title: Minimal Female School Dropout Rates
description: In 2016, only 0.03% of primary school-aged girls were out of school in France, reflecting one of the lowest dropout rates globally.

title: Low Internal Displacement Figures
description: By 2022, France reported only 10 internally displaced people, showcasing its stability and effective management of internal affairs.
